with a very white forehead and tousled hair, suffering — they said — from tuberculosis; once a guest — they said —

of the Dalai Lama; in love — they said — with one of the upper-form girls, a niece of the white-haired, blue-eyed headmistress, whose tidy little office was so cozy with its blue wallpaper and white Dutch stove.

